oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Dunlap house
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Knoxville Sentinel
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Home of Annie and Mae Dunlap, Woodlawn Pike, Knoxville, TN. The home was built using materials from the James White cabin. In the 1950s many of the logs were used in the rebuilding of the James White Fort. During the Depression, Annie and Mae Dunlap provided a home for their niece Irene Smelser and her children Laura Smelser (later Wuesthoff) and Francis E. Smelser (Bud).
